headline: Heard on the Street Wednesday Recap: Tech Check
summary: Tech stocks were broadly weaker. The Nasdaq Composite lost 0.9%, and the S&P 500 dropped 0.5%. The Dow Jones Industrial Average shed 334 points, or 0.7%. Netflix shares declined 10%. Its quarterly profit was below expectations, though revenue from its advertising business picked up.

headline: Capital One (COF) Net Profit Margin Falls to 4%, Challenging Bullish Growth Narratives
summary: Capital One Financial (COF) reported current net profit margins of 4%, down sharply from last year’s 15.3%, while earnings have declined 19.7% per year over the past five years. Despite this pressure on profitability, forecasts point to a strong rebound, with revenue expected to jump 20.5% per year and annual earnings growth projected at 51.4%, both comfortably ahead of the broader US market’s outlook. Investors face a complex picture, weighing short-term earnings setbacks and insider selling...
